properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 8 at 3:18PM CST until January 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...SNOW TONIGHT INTO THURSDAY ALONG THE NORTH SHORE...
...MIX OF SNOW AND FREEZING DRIZZLE IN NORTHERN WISCONSIN
THURSDAY...

.An area of low pressure and off lake winds will cause snow to
develop along the North Shore this evening continuing into
Thursday. The highest accumulation will occur in the higher
terrain just inland from Lake Superior. Light snow and freezing
drizzle will be possible on Thursday over northwest Wisconsin with
some light icing possible.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation expected. Total snow accumulations
of up to one inch and ice accumulations of a light glaze.

* WHERE...Bayfield, Ashland, Iron, Sawyer and Price Counties.
This includes the Tribal Lands of the Red Cliff Band and the
Bad River Reservation.

* WHEN...From 8 AM to 6 PM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM TO 6 PM CST THURSDAY
